title: Fortios: DHCP scope
agents: special
catalog: network/fortigate
license: GPLv2
distribution: check_mk
description:
 This check monitors the DHCP scopes of a Fortigate firewall.
 It changes the status to {crit} or {warn}, 
 depending on the threshold values set.
 If conflicts are detected, the status also turns to {warn}.
 The default values are 80 and 90% of the size of the IP range.
 The check shows some data about the scope.


 The special agent is required for this check, 
 which can be configured via “FortiOS”.

discovery:
 One service per DHCP scope is created.
